Abolished 1.4.1965 and added to the London borough of Barnet.

Transferred from MIddlesex to Hertfordshire on 1.4.1889. See also 
    Table 2, notes (a) and (b). Abolished 1.4.1965 and added to the London borough of Barnet.

In 1889 the parts of the parish of South Mimms in the urban districts 
    of Barnet and East Barnet Valley became part of Hertfordshire, In 1894 these 
    areas became parts of the parishes of South Mimms Urban and Monken Hadley respectively and thereaffter South Mimms was again wholly in Middlesex. See also Table 2, 
    notes (c) and (e).
Abolished 1.4.1965 and added to the London borough of Barnet.
